		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Barbarian SHAMAN: Levels 1-26</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:JCA1183@AOL.com">Bobslob</a> | 
		            4/27/2001 8:50:36 AM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Wanna become a Shaman of the Tribunal? I myself am level 55 right now, but I dont want to write a guide that will spoil everything. Therefore I will write a guide until level 26, where you should get a good idea of what you want to do with your shaman and how to use a shaman. (Barbarians Only)<BR>
<BR>
CREATION--<BR>
<BR>
Since you alrdy have really good stats, add all the points you can into Wisdom. You should only be able to add 25 outta 30. Add the last 5 into Charisma, or Dexterity, or agility. Then choose your face, because you dont want a butt ugly shaman walking around. (I chose the blonde &lt;Male&gt; face)<BR>
<BR>
Levels 1-6--<BR>
<BR>
~~MEM YOUR SPELLS~~<BR>
Go into your guild and turn in your note. The guild is behind the bank. Not directly behind it, but walk a little ways until you get into a little alley to your right and your guild will be to the left when you enter the 2nd alley. <BR>
Train 2 points into 1h blunt, 1 into alter, and 1 into evoc.<BR>
<BR>
Now go to everfrost peaks. From there, follow the only way out from the gate till you reach the newb area, which is between 2 path that lead left and right. Fight everything that cons even to you until you hit 2. At level 2, fight polar bears, spiderlings, wolves, etc,.. until level 3. At level 3 you should have enough money from selling polar bear skins, and all your loot, to buy your first level spells. If you want to get yourself started in Tailoring, YES I said tailoring at level 4 with an untwinked guy, then save up all your practice points until level 4. Fight creatures in everfrost until level 4. (See bottom of this section for Tailoring guide of levels 4-6. At level 4, you can now fight at least 3 polar bears at a time, for alot of EXP. Keep fighting masses of polar bears until you hit 5, and at 5, get your new spells, (check out everlore's magic section for complete listing on spells)and fight like 10 polar bears at a time, they only have about 40hp so melee and a few casts of frost rift should kill them. If you cant make these huhge trains of bears for yourself, then get a SOW from a shaman or druid, and run around everfrost getting all the bears you can. Thats what I did to get to level 6....<BR>
<BR>
TAILORING-- levels 4-6<BR>
If you want to become a tailor like I did, then save all the wolf and bear pelts you can. SEll and the polar bear and While Wolf skin that yu find becasue they sell for 1.2 gold or so. Train all the points you can into tailoring and get all the money you have and bring it with you (should be at least 5 gold, and al the ruined pelts you have to the merchants by the Zone Line in Everfrost. Buy a Small Sewing kit, (unsure of price) and a ca pattern. PLace 1 pelt in at a time and the 1 pattern in at a time and combine. You should get a cap, and you can sell it for 1.5 gold. The pattern costs 6 silver, and if you are using the pelts you got from kills then you do the math -- I got 5 plat this way and a full set of patchwork armor for myself. And my skill got up to about 30 or so.<BR>
<BR>
LEVELS 6-12<BR>
<BR>
Ok, now ur doing pretty good. Go to QEYNOS, get a bind there, and then go to BLACKBURROW. Fight in a group there, until level 9. (IN your group you should be fighting scrawney gnolls, regulatr gnolls, and maybe even a burly gnoll)<BR>
At level 9, you get SOW! WOOT WOOT. Go to Halas, buy your new spells, and DOTs (Tainted Breath is the most important spell at this level) and go back to BB. Once your there, charge 1 plat for SOWs if you wanna waste time and get money. But, if you dont, then go fight Giant Snakes in BlackBurrow. Ask someone to lead you there becasue I dont feel like typing that much right now lol. But fight giant snakes that con even/blue to tou until level 12. The snakes drop Giant Snake fangs, and poison sacks, they both sell for about 5 gold each. But watch out for gnol trains in that room, thats a train station where alot of high level trains go through.<BR>
<BR>
Levels 12-15<BR>
<BR>
At these levels, I got a port to Gfay, go a bind to the spires, and went to The Estate of Unrest. (ask someone how to get there, very dangerous trip btw) Once there, immediatly get a group and fight death beetles, tormented dead, greater skellis, jackolanterns, etc,. (&quot;yard trash&quot;) Until level 15. DO NOT GO TO HALAS UNTIL LEVEL 15 TO GET YOUR LEVEL 14 SPELLS, becasue at 15 you get dodge. Train 5-10 points into dodge, and whatch it go up. A piece of advice. If someone calls a train, for gods sake do not help them, or be anywhere the zone line. You will die, and/or your group will. (Unless the train has 4 or less creatures that or even, or 1 or 2 yellows at most)<BR>
<BR>
Levels 15-19<BR>
<BR>
At these levels, EXP in unrest slowed, so I went to Oasis. Solo crocs that are even or blue, or fight in a group that kills crocs. I myself fought in a very secret area, which was so good that me and my grp levels 3 levels in 2 hours.I will not tell you where it is, but I will give you clues:  orc camp (not highway), gypsies, and pillars. At this place, there was a pull every 2 min of undead, crocs, orcs, like every creature in oasis cept giants. So just fight here until level 19. Then go to Halas and buy your new DOTs and Spells. <BR>
<BR>
LEvels 19-22<BR>
<BR>
For these 22 levels lol, I fought in Lake of Ill Omen. Here I went to the mill and SOLOed Sabertooth cats, iksars, sarnek flunkies, and undead for 2 levels. Believe me, fighting sarneks here isnt that good exp, becasue ur in grps that are all red to you and you are basically fighting evens and yellows. So just fight sarneks from level 21-22<BR>
<BR>
LEVEL 23. At this level, I decided to get a work on my totemic armor. I went to LFAY, and camped the orc chief for his tougue. (totemic boots)I camped him in a grp with a guild mate and got about 3/4 a blue bub each kill, and te spawn was about 5 min so I leveled to 23 real fast. After abut 1 days of camping, (reached 23 on the 1st day) I got the tougue, put it in the bank, and ran to SK. <BR>
<BR>
LEVELS 23- 26<BR>
<BR>
I fought in SK these levels. To fight here, get a gnoll grp and kill gnolls until your level 25 in a grp. You will get REALLY good loot and money. Loot includes 1-3 plat, FS weopons, Daggers of Droppings, Gnoll lariats, and GNoll hide armor. I got about 100 plat for 2 days of camping these gnolls. At 24 run to halas, and buy your spells, then run back and get another gnoll grp until 25. At level 25, the gnolls will become even, yellow, and red to you. Solo the Evens and sometimes yellow gnolls if you want to, but you can also go into the grp until level 26. At 26, just plain solo the gnolls, its better exp.<BR>
<BR>
EQUIPMENT TIPS<BR>
<BR>
-- Body<BR>
When I was in Qeynos, a long, long time ago, there was someone there selling banded armor for 0.5 plat per AC. Bless his soul, I bought a full set of banded except a head becasue the polar bear head looked awesome. <BR>
<BR>
-- Jewelry <BR>
Get your guild to help you whenever you can for this one. Wisdom, and only wisdom earings and rings. But if you can, buy +4 wisdome and +2 str rings. Also, buy +15 hp and mana bracelets when your levels 15- 25. And as you can afford the jewelry, buy +3 wisdom, then +6 wisdome jewlery.<BR>
<BR>
Totemic Armor tips<BR>
<BR>
one word : GUILD<BR>
<BR>
Get a good guild with people levels 20-40 or so, and tell them to help you with the quest. The easiest totemic armor to do though is the totemic arms because in Unrest, there are usally ghoul carrions everywhere in carrion ghoul corpses. And Charger hoof chips lieing everywhere in SK.<BR>
I cant offer much more help for totemic, becasue I did the armor quests at level 28 =)  But do the totemic arms quest several times and sell them for 150 plat each. I made lots of money this way  casue the totemic arms quest is pretty easy. And a good way to get dufretite and ask a high level shaman for his left over dufretite, or ask your guild again.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Mezol-- Level 55 Shaman of <BR>
Luclin Server <BR>

